			 Tutorial: Using the hierarchyid Data Type 

					 
								 03/14/2017 
							 2 minutes to read 
							 
								 Contributors 
								 
											 
								 

					 In this article 
						 THIS TOPIC APPLIES TO: SQL Server (starting with 2008) Azure SQL Database Azure SQL Data Warehouse  Parallel Data Warehouse  This tutorial is intended for users who are experienced with  Transact-SQL, but are new to the  hierarchyid  data type.   
 What You Will Learn 
 This tutorial is divided into two lessons:   
 Lesson 1: Converting a Table to a Hierarchical Structure In this lesson, you take an existing employee table that is structured as a parent/child hierarchy and move the data into a new table that represents the hierarchy by using the  hierarchyid  data type. This lesson requires the    AdventureWorks2012  sample database.   
